{"lemma":"أُجْرَةٌ","slug":"أُجْرَةٌ","root":"#.ج.ر","root_slug":"_-ج-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/_-ج-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n268","n275","n5380"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A3%D9%8F%D8%AC%D9%92%D8%B1%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"rent"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"reward, recompense"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"compensation, pay, wages"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Compare أَجَرَ (ʔajara, “to reward, to hire out, to rent out”)."},"ipa":["/ʔud͡ʒ.ra/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n268","headword_ar":"اَجَرَهُ","root":"Ajr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, Msb, K,) which latter form of the aor., though known to most of the lexicologists, is disacknowledged by a few of them, (TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ajorN","text_ar":"اَجْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, Msb;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=jrhu","text_ar":"ا=جرهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, Msb, K,) a form disacknowledged by As, but said by some to be the more chaste of the two, of the form"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^afoEala","text_ar":"اَفْعَلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", not"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faAEala","text_ar":"فَاعَلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as IKtt by evident inadvertence makes it to be by saying that its aor. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yuw^aAjiru","text_ar":"يُوَاجِرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iyjaArN","text_ar":"اـِيجَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(God, S, A, Mgh, Msb, and a man, Mgh)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"recompensed, compensated,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rewarded, him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Mgh, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ealay maA faEala","text_ar":"عَلَي مَا فَعَلَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for what he had done."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) [See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ajorN","text_ar":"اَجْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", below.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ujira fulaAnN xamosapF mino waladihi","text_ar":"اُجِرَ فُلَانٌ خَمْسَةً مِنْ وَلَدِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one became entitled to a reward for five of his children,"},{"kind":"text","text":"by their death, (for it is believed that the Muslim will be rewarded in Paradise for a child that has died in infancy)], (S,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ujira waladahu","text_ar":"اُجِرَ وَلَدَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ujira fiy A^awolaAdihi","text_ar":"اُجِرَ فِي اَوْلَادِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) mean that his children died, and became [causes of] his reward. (S, A, K.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ajarahu","text_ar":"اَجَرَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He served him for hire, pay,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wages;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he became his hired man,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hireling."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K.) So in the Kur xxviii. 27. (TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ajarahu","text_ar":"اَجَرَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (L, Msb, K,) and"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ajorN","text_ar":"اَجْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (L, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He let him"},{"kind":"text","text":"(namely his slave)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"on hire,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for pay,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wages;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, * Msb, * K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=jrhu","text_ar":"ا=جرهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iyjaArN","text_ar":"اـِيجَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; ('Eyn, Mgh, Msb, K;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=jrhu","text_ar":"ا=جرهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mw^Ajrp","text_ar":"مواجرة"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) all these are good forms of speech, used by the Arabs: (L:) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=jrhu","text_ar":"ا=جرهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"having for its inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mw^Ajrp","text_ar":"مواجرة"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he appointed him"},{"kind":"text","text":"(namely another man)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hire, pay,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wages, for his work;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mj, Mgh;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he engaged with him to give him hire, pay,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wages;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, Mgh, Msb;) and can have only one objective complement: whereas, ↓ when it is of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^afoEala","text_ar":"اَفْعَلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"it is doubly trans.; (Mgh, Msb;) so that one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mamoluwkahu","text_ar":"مَمْلُوكَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=jaraniy","text_ar":"ا=جَرَنِي","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He let me his slave on hire."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh.) One also says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ajara Ald~aAra","text_ar":"اَجَرَ الدَّارَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ajorN","text_ar":"اَجْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He let the house on hire;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~aAra","text_ar":"الدَّارَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=jr","text_ar":"ا=جر","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", [inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iyjaArN","text_ar":"اـِيجَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] (Msb, TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~aAra","text_ar":"الدَّارَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=jrhu","text_ar":"ا=جرهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", [inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iyjaArN","text_ar":"اـِيجَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He let to him the house on hire:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Mgh, Msb:) the latter verb being of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^afoEala","text_ar":"اَفْعَلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", not of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faAEala","text_ar":"فَاعَلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (A, Mgh, Msb:) and the vulgar say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waAjara","text_ar":"وَاجَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) some, however, say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~aAra","text_ar":"الدَّارَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=jarotu","text_ar":"ا=جَرْتُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muw^aAjarapN","text_ar":"مُوَاجَرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", making the verb of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fAEl","text_ar":"فاعل"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb, TA:) some also say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~aAra zayod~aA","text_ar":"الدَّارَ زَيْدَّا"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=jarotu","text_ar":"ا=جَرْتُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I let the house to Zeyd"},{"kind":"text","text":"], inverting the order of the words: (Msb, TA:) and the lawyers say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~aAra mino zayodK","text_ar":"الدَّارَ مِنْ زَيْدٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=jarotu","text_ar":"ا=جَرْتُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in the same sense, like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biEotu mino zayodK Ald~aAri","text_ar":"بِعْتُ مِنْ زَيْدٍ الدَّارِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means the same as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biEotu zayodAF","text_ar":"بِعْتُ زَيْداً"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~aAra","text_ar":"الدَّارَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Msb: [but in the Mgh, the like of this is said to be vulgar.])"}],"source_refs":["S","Mgh","Msb","K","TA","A","L"]},{"entry_id":"n275","headword_ar":"اُجْرَةٌ","root":"Ajr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ajorN","text_ar":"اَجْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in three places."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n5380","headword_ar":"اجرّهُ","root":"jr","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He pierced him with the spear and left it in him so that he dragged it along:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:) or so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ajr~hu Alr~umoHa","text_ar":"اجرّهُ الرُّمْحَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (A, Msb:) as though [meaning]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he made him to drag along the spear."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He put the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jariyr","text_ar":"جَرِير"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e. the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rope, upon his neck."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Har p. 308.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ajr~hu jariyrahu","text_ar":"اجرّهُ جَرِيرَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made him to drag along his rope;"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning,] (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he left him to pasture by himself, where he pleased:"},{"kind":"text","text":"a prov. (L.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ajr~hu rasanahu","text_ar":"اجرّهُ رَسَنَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made him to drag along his halter;"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning,] (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he left him to do as he would:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he left him to his affair."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ajr~hu Ald~ayona","text_ar":"اجرّهُ الدَّيْنَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He deferred for him the payment of the debt:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he left the debt to remain owed by him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ajr~hu","text_ar":"اجرّهُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^agaAniY~a","text_ar":"اَغَانِىَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He sang songs to him consecutively, successively,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"uninterruptedly;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taAbaEahaA","text_ar":"تَابَعَهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, K, TA:) or (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he sang to him a song and then followed it up with consecutive songs."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA.) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ajr~","text_ar":"اجرّ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lisaAna AlfaSiyli","text_ar":"لِسَانَ الفَصِيلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ajr~ AlfaSiyla","text_ar":"اجرّ الفَصِيلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (As, K, *) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ijoraArN","text_ar":"اـِجْرَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlfaSiyla","text_ar":"الفَصِيلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jar~a","text_ar":"جَرَّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (As K, *) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jar~N","text_ar":"جَرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He slit the tongue of the young weaned camel, that it might not suck the teat:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, TA:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ijoraAru AlfaSiyli","text_ar":"اـِجْرَارُ الفَصِيلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the slitting the tongue of the young weaned camel, and tying upon it a piece of stick, that it may not suck the teat;"},{"kind":"text","text":"because it drags along the piece of stick with its tongue: or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA_ijoraAru","text_ar":"الاـِجْرَارُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alt~afoliyku","text_ar":"التَّفْلِيكُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", signifying (assumed tropical:)  a pastor's"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"making, of coarse hair, a thing like the whirl,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hemispherical head, of a spindle, and then boring the tongue of the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"young"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"camel, and inserting it therein, that it may not suck the teat:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so say some: (ISk, TA:) the animal upon which the operation has been performed is said to be ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"majoruwrN","text_ar":"مَجْرُورٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mujar~N","text_ar":"مُجَرٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) [But sometimes ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jar~a","text_ar":"جَرَّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies merely"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He drew away"},{"kind":"text","text":"a young camel from its mother: see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaliy~apN","text_ar":"خَلِيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaliY~N","text_ar":"خَلِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in three places.] ―         -b7-  Hence,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ajr~ lisaAnahu","text_ar":"اجرّ لِسَانَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He prevented him from speaking."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) 'Amr Ibn-MaadeeKerib Ez-Zubeydee says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"falawo A^an~a qawomiY A^anoTaqatoniY rimaAHuhumo\n                      \n                     \n                        naTaqotu wal`kin~a Alr~imaAHa A^jar~ati"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And if the spears of my people had made me to speak, I had spoken; but the spears have prevented speech"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: i. e., had they fought, and shown their valour, I had mentioned that, and gloried in it, (S,) or in them; (TA;) but their spears have prevented my tongue from speaking, by their flight. (S, * TA.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ajr~","text_ar":"اجرّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as an intrans. verb: see 8. ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ajr~t Albiy^oru","text_ar":"اجرّت البِيْرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The well was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, such as is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaruwr","text_ar":"جَرُور"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Ibn-Buzurj, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","K","A","Msb","TA","ISk"]}]},"classical_definitions":{"source":"hawramani","url":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/%D8%A3%D8%AC%D8%B1%D8%A9/","headword_ar":"أجرة المِثل","entries":[{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_27","lexicon_en":"Al-Barakatī, al-Taʿrīfāt al-Fiqhīya (d. 1975 CE)","lexicon_ar":"التعريفات الفقهيّة للبركتي","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=46530#c2fafc","body_html":"<span class=\"title1\">أجرة المِثل: </span><span>هي الأجرة التي قدرها أهل الخبرة ممن لا غرضَ لهم.</span>"}]}}